 :tx/rationale "Create task: AR-3 (REVISED): Unified spec_graph_neighbors — single VAET-based graph traversal serving BOTH knowledge_relevance_scan AND session trace buffer (INV-BILATERAL-002, INV-STORE-004, INV-GUIDANCE-024). BACKGROUND: Merges AR-3 + RECON-SPEC-GRAPH (t-827dbbb8). One graph traversal function, two consumers: (1) knowledge_relevance_scan calls it at observe/task-create time to surface related entities via the spec graph (fixing the lexical-gap failure mode), (2) SessionTraceBuffer.record calls it to populate trace neighbors. The function uses VAET reverse-ref index (INV-STORE-004: 'reverse reference traversal') — the index was literally designed for this purpose. APPROACH: (1) spec_graph_neighbors(store: &Store, spec_ref_ids: &[String]) -> Vec<(EntityId, f64)>: For each ref ID, resolve to EntityId via AVET on :element/id. For each resolved spec entity, VAET reverse lookup: find all entities with :task/traces-to or :impl/implements pointing to it. Score = 1.0 / ln(2 + ref_count) (IDF: penalize ubiquitous specs). For 1-hop: follow :spec/traces-to from spec entity to neighbor specs, VAET on those (score *= 0.5). Deduplicate by max score. Cap at top-10. (2) Wire into knowledge_relevance_scan: after existing keyword search, run spec_graph_neighbors on any spec refs found in the input text via parse_spec_refs. Merge results: for each entity, final_score = max(keyword_score, graph_score). This is the L-infinity norm — a match on ANY dimension surfaces the connection. (3) Wire into SessionTraceBuffer.record: same function, results stored in TraceDatom.neighbors. (4) extract_spec_namespace(spec_ref: &str) -> &str: parse 'INV-TOPOLOGY-001' → 'TOPOLOGY'. Used by both trace buffer (for neighborhood) and concentration detector. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Two entities both tracing to INV-INTERFACE-001 → neighbors with score > 0. (B) REGRESSION: observation about 'TSV output format INV-INTERFACE-001' surfaces ACP EPIC (which also traces to INV-INTERFACE-001). (C) IDF: INV-STORE-001 (50+ refs) scores lower than INV-TOPOLOGY-005 (2 refs). (D) 1-hop: entity tracing to INV-BUDGET-007 is neighbor of entity tracing to INV-INTERFACE-001 if INV-BUDGET-007 traces-to INV-INTERFACE-001. (E) L-infinity: max(keyword=0, graph=0.8) = 0.8 (graph saves the day). (F) Performance: <500μs (VAET is O(1) per entity). DEPENDS-ON: AR-1. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs"
